Uses of Class
com.here.android.mpa.mapping.MapObject

  • Packages that use MapObject 
    Package Description
    com.here.android.mpa.mapping
    The mapping package provides classes, interfaces, and enumerations that display an interactive map, and related functionality that allows your application to create and add map content.

    • Uses of MapObject in com.here.android.mpa.mapping

      Subclasses of MapObject in com.here.android.mpa.mapping 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  MapCircle
      Represents a MapObject in the shape of a circle.
      class  MapContainer
      Represents a container that determines the stacking order of objects on a Map.
      class  MapGeoModel
      A MapGeoModel is a GeoCoordinate mesh displayed on a map.
      class  MapLabeledMarker
      This class represents a labeled icon on the Map.
      class  MapLocalModel
      Represents a relative local coordinate mesh displayed on a map.
      class  MapMarker
      Represents a marker used to display an icon at a geographical position on a map.
      class  MapModelObject
      Base class for MapLocalModel and MapGeoModel.
      class  MapPolygon
      A graphical representation of a GeoPolygon to be rendered on a map.
      class  MapPolyline
      A graphical representation of a GeoPolyline that can be rendered on a map.
      class  MapRoute
      Represents a Route that can be displayed on a Map.
      class  MapScreenMarker
      Represents a marker used to display an icon at a screen position on a map.
      Methods in com.here.android.mpa.mapping that return MapObject 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      MapObject MapObject.resetVisibleMask(boolean set)
      Resets the visibility bit mask of this MapObject to be either 1s or 0s.
      MapObject MapRoute.resetVisibleMask(boolean set)
      This API is not supported by MapRoute as MapRoute's visibility for specific zoom level cannot be specified.
      MapObject MapObject.setOverlayType(MapOverlayType type)
      Sets the display order in which this MapObject appears relating to other layers of the map.
      MapObject MapObject.setReserveOverlayType(MapOverlayType type)
      Currently this method is only supported for MapLabeledMarker objects.
      MapObject MapObject.setVisible(boolean isVisible)
      Sets whether the visibility of the MapObject on the map is enabled.
      MapObject MapObject.setVisibleMask(int level)
      Sets the visibility bit mask of this MapObject at the specified zoom level.
      MapObject MapRoute.setVisibleMask(int level)
      This API is not supported by MapRoute as MapRoute's visibility for specific zoom level cannot be specified.
      MapObject MapObject.setVisibleMask(int levelStart, int levelEnd)
      Sets the visibility bit mask of this MapObject for the specified range of zoom levels.
      MapObject MapRoute.setVisibleMask(int levelStart, int levelEnd)
      This API is not supported by MapRoute as MapRoute's visibility for specific zoom level cannot be specified.
      MapObject MapObject.setZIndex(int index)
      Sets a z-index (stacking order) value for this MapObject.
      MapObject MapObject.unsetVisibleMask(int level)
      Unsets the visibility bit mask of this MapObject at the specified zoom level.
      MapObject MapRoute.unsetVisibleMask(int level)
      This API is not supported by MapRoute as MapRoute's visibility for specific zoom level cannot be specified.
